<subSubSection id="2B0D670033F18B32B9C6D432C09FCF7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="method">
<paragraph id="F74F0D58A91E7F0E6728B92E298B48DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A615731845546BD1E53913D368E7053" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 °C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine for 7-8 minutes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8F4453319EDB4FAABC4280C66BF95BFE" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="observations">
<paragraph id="C583145BBB64669C50830DD4C68C160C" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF26ECB379A6763687801CEA7B0ACB12" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="FB16382D70DBAE53443FCEF5A562DAAF" authority="subsp. glanduliferum" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hieracium glanduliferum subsp. glanduliferum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="glanduliferum" subSpecies="glanduliferum">Hieracium glanduliferum subsp. glanduliferum</taxonomicName>
is a south European alpine species with isolated populations that occur in the northern Apennines on Monte Prado, Monte Cusna, and Monte Cimone (
<bibRefCitation id="60C7F89A7D8A4F8EB61A2760EE2529D6" author="Foggi, B" journalOrPublisher="Memorie, serie B" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="77 - 81" refId="B16" refString="Foggi, B, Ricceri, C, 1989. Contributo alla conoscenza della flora orofila dell'Appennino Settentrionale. Atti della Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali. Memorie, serie B 96: 77 - 81" title="Contributo alla conoscenza della flora orofila dell'Appennino Settentrionale. Atti della Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali." volume="96" year="1989">Foggi and Ricceri 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="011F10F3ED38E116C247942DF1882242" author="Gottschlich, G" editor="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="3, Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1138 - 1195" refId="B18" refString="Gottschlich, G, 2018. Hieracium. In: Pignatti, S, Ed., Flora d'Italia Vol. 3, Edagricole, Bologna: 1138 - 1195" title="Hieracium." volumeTitle="Flora d'Italia Vol." year="2018">Gottschlich 2018</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first count for this taxon for Italy, whereas other counts have been published for 
<taxonomicName id="84E65C5D1E1CAAEDBC91566FAC3F6A96" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hieracium glanduliferum subsp. piliferum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="glanduliferum" subSpecies="piliferum">Hieracium glanduliferum Hoppe subsp. piliferum</taxonomicName>
Hoppe ex 
<normalizedToken id="20A0729CCD4E21F524AC26F3CE8679DD" originalValue="Nägeli">Naegeli</normalizedToken>
&amp; Peter, for which two different chromosome numbers have been reported so far, 2 
<emphasis id="33D54EC63BD06A029D3DAC5426329012" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 3 
<emphasis id="1C218DB137DB907030EC7558F295193F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x</emphasis>
= 27 from Italy, Switzerland, and Austria (
<bibRefCitation id="2FF36B2500C6941C070EA1A56F5133EE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1977.tb04204.x" author="Scholte, G" editor="Loeve, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="258 - 259" refId="B25" refString="Scholte, G, 1977. Reports by G. Scholte. In: Loeve, A, Ed., IOPB chromosome number reports LVI. Taxon 26: 258 - 259, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1977.tb04204.x" title="Reports by G. Scholte." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1977.tb04204.x" volume="26" volumeTitle="IOPB chromosome number reports LVI." year="1977">Scholte 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FBF05D9AA0181B50070B6F431DC034BC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" author="Chrtek Jr, J" journalOrPublisher="Annals of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="161 - 178" refId="B10" refString="Chrtek Jr, J, Zahradnicek, J, Krak, K, Fehrer, J, 2009. Genome size in Hieracium subgenus Hieracium (Asteraceae) is strongly correlated with major phylogenetic groups. Annals of Botany 104: 161 - 178, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" title="Genome size in Hieracium subgenus Hieracium (Asteraceae) is strongly correlated with major phylogenetic groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" volume="104" year="2009">Chrtek et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 2 
<emphasis id="1057F112C80930E64C55715EDEF8542C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 4 
<emphasis id="DA42F112BDFAB209070C121A9FC7C718" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x</emphasis>
= 36 from Austria and Slovakia (
<bibRefCitation id="D51A9A3E4C221FD89E3AD3BEE1E8A639" author="Mraz, P" journalOrPublisher="Biologia (Bratislava)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="29 - 36" refId="B22" refString="Mraz, P, 2003. Hieracium piliferum group (Asteraceae) in the West Carpathians. Biologia (Bratislava) 58: 29 - 36" title="Hieracium piliferum group (Asteraceae) in the West Carpathians." volume="58" year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="192EF4627E72C0D3C241200ED58C4942" originalValue="Mráz">Mraz</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7496E94C167B0231D828C895CFB71CB6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" author="Chrtek Jr, J" journalOrPublisher="Annals of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="161 - 178" refId="B10" refString="Chrtek Jr, J, Zahradnicek, J, Krak, K, Fehrer, J, 2009. Genome size in Hieracium subgenus Hieracium (Asteraceae) is strongly correlated with major phylogenetic groups. Annals of Botany 104: 161 - 178, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" title="Genome size in Hieracium subgenus Hieracium (Asteraceae) is strongly correlated with major phylogenetic groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" volume="104" year="2009">Chrtek et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
, in all sources under the name 
<taxonomicName id="1962108D45715A40B2A4B10B6FBBB5D7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hieracium piliferum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piliferum">
<emphasis id="11FB5A4F4384A8331B8D8A0F2001A8EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hieracium piliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hoppe).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="95F60021352C11FB03381FE36FC559EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
S. Orsenigo, A. 
<normalizedToken id="D608C9C078C2C799A1811EFD125572AA" originalValue="Giacò">Giaco</normalizedToken>
, G. Astuti
</paragraph>
